DataElement.preferredName: Neck Lymph Node Level Anatomic Site
DataElement.preferredDefinition: Text term that represents the anatomic level of neck lymph nodes using criteria defined by AJCC.

DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: Classification of neck lymph nodes into anatomic levels, using criteria defined as Levels I-VII and Other by AJCC.

ObjectClass.preferredDefinition: The region that connects the head to the rest of the body.:A rounded mass of lymphatic tissue that is surrounded by a capsule of connective tissue. Lymph glands filter lymph (lymphatic fluid), and they store lymphocytes (white blood cells). They are located along lymphatic vessels. Also called a lymph node.

Concepts.definition: The region that connects the head to the rest of the body.

A bean-shaped organ surrounded by a connective tissue capsule. It is part of the lymphatic system and is found throughout the body. It is composed predominantly of lymphocytes and its main function is immune protection.

Property.preferredDefinition: A position on a scale measuring intensity, quality, or amount.  (NCI)

Concepts.definition: A position on a scale measuring intensity, quality, or amount.

ConceptualDomain.preferredDefinition: indication of the presence and extent of disease.

ValueDomain.preferredName: Neck Lymph Node Level Anatomic Site
ValueDomain.preferredDefinition: Named locations of or within the body.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A lymph node located in the retropharyngeal space behind the upper part of the pharynx.

Concepts.definition: A lymph node located in the retropharyngeal space behind the upper part of the pharynx.

PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Neck Lymph Node Boundary Level III

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Neck Lymph Node Boundary Level III
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The following anatomical structures define the neck lymph node boundary for level III: Superior: horizontal plane defined by the inferior body of the hyoid; inferior: horizontal plane defined by the inferior border of the cricoid cartilage; anterior (medial): lateral border of the sternohyoid muscle; posterior (lateral): lateral border of the sternocleidomastoid or sensory branches of the cervical plexus. (AJCC 8th ed.)

Concepts.longName: Neck Lymph Node Boundary Level III
Concepts.definition: The following anatomical structures define the neck lymph node boundary for level III: Superior: horizontal plane defined by the inferior body of the hyoid; inferior: horizontal plane defined by the inferior border of the cricoid cartilage; anterior (medial): lateral border of the sternohyoid muscle; posterior (lateral): lateral border of the sternocleidomastoid or sensory branches of the cervical plexus.
